original:
The specific pulse form utilized in magnetic stimulation appears to significantly influence its behavioral effects. For instance, a pulsed magnetic field designed for spectroscopic magnetic resonance imaging (MRI), known as Low Field Magnetic Stimulation, has been shown to temporarily enhance mood in patients with bipolar disorder. In contrast, another MRI pulse did not demonstrate any noticeable effects on mood.
